---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="about"
  description="about mikael ristmets — architect, photographer, barista."
>
  <article class="container">
    <header class="page-head">
      <p class="eyebrow">⁂ &nbsp; about</p>
      <h1>mikael ristmets</h1>
      <hr class="rule rule--short" />
    </header>

    <div class="prose">
      <p class="lede">
        <span class="red">mina usun, et arhitektuur pole üksnes ruumikujundamise
        tööriist, vaid ka ühiskonna, misläbi on võimalik luua paremat
        elu kõigile.</span>
      </p>
      <p class="lede">
        <span class="blue">architecture is not just something we use to design
        the space around us, but something that also shapes society,
        which allows for the creation of better lives for everyone.</span>
      </p>

      <p>
        this site is an ongoing archive of work — architecture, furniture,
        installations, photography, video, art, music, and coffee. the
        homepage is a single newest-first feed of everything. each
        section is a filtered slice of the same archive.
      </p>

      <h2>colophon</h2>
      <p>
        set in a system monospace stack. built with
        <a href="https://astro.build">astro</a>, statically rendered.
        all entries live as markdown files next to their images in this
        repository.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-head {
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-6);
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--sp-3);
    max-width: var(--measure);
  }
  .page-head h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: var(--fs-2xl);
    line-height: var(--lh-tight);
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }
  .lede {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-md);
    color: var(--fg);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
</style>
